data.description: **Ask me how to buy this home with no money down!**  Exquisite newly remodeled 3-bed, 2-bath home on a scenic and well-maintained golf course!  Featuring a long screened-in porch with swing bed overlooking the fenced backyard and golf course, and a dreamy outdoor kitchen/tiki bar with hot tub, this beautiful turnkey home evokes a sense of quality craftsmanship.  Stepping indoors you'll discover new luxury vinyl plank flooring throughout, new ceiling fans and blinds, fresh paint, and a welcoming interior that seamlessly connects the living areas.  The living room opens to the dining room with garden doors that provide access to the rear porch and offer a lovely view of the backyard and beyond.  Adjacent is the gorgeous upgraded eat-in island kitchen that includes new s/s appliances, cabinetry, shelving, bar, beverage refrigerator, and plenty of space for casual dining.  You'll find roomy guest bedrooms and a generous primary suite with walk-in closet and updated ensuite bath with a double vanity, water closet and tub/shower combo.  There's ample storage space throughout the 2,134 sf home and a large indoor laundry room.  Other highlights include new exterior paint, shutters, fencing, paved driveway and side-entry two car garage, giving this .60-acre lot even greater curb appeal.  Another bonus is that the home already passed a 5-point inspection!  Located in Chiefland Country Estates, the property is just minutes to schools, restaurants and stores, and backs onto Chiefland Golf and Country Club where the members recently spent hundreds of thousands of dollars renovating and improving the course.  Chiefland, “Gem of the Suwannee Valley,” is a laidback community known for Manatee Springs State Park and the Suwannee River.  It's ideally situated about 40 miles from Gainesville and 30 miles from Cedar Key on the Gulf of Mexico.  This home is ideal for golfers, snorkelers, boating enthusiasts or those who just appreciate a well-appointed home with high-end finishes.  If this is you, you'll want to schedule a private tour while it's still available!
